            "body": "> Using AI is fine, but please review the logic and text yourself before asking for review. There is way too much verbosity here. Clean up the explanation, and code, so that it is simple and meaningful. And after all the verbosity here, the actual approach in this PR is basically just a workaround/hack, and not even a good one. We need your help to narrow down AI output to more meaningful and less noisy results.\n\nYes this is a bandaid, to avoid the crash for the time being,I wanted to suggest a couple of better solutions, before touching in a  significant way this part of the code. I think to better fix this, we need to agree on a road and then move in that direction. The problem here is that there is no space, for the windows, and we need to put them in another buffer or tab, or we need to limit the maximum number of split available in a buffer so we do not encounter this problem, I just wanted to discuss it with you first, and if you think is a good idea I will implement it. ",
